            <td>Continuous Integration 
            <td>Continuous Integration is a software development practice that involves merging code changes into a shared repository to detect and address integration issues. This practice is typically performed daily. Automated tools are used to assist with each integration and to identify any errors that may be present.
            <td>Martin Fowler. ( 01 May 2006). Continuous Integration. Martinfowler. https://martinfowler.com/articles/continuousIntegration.html<br/><br/>
              Spiwoks, R. et al. (2023) ‘Continuous Integration for the Software and the Firmware of the New ATLAS Muon-Central- Trigger-Processor Interface (MUCTPI)’, IEEE Transactions on Nuclear Science, Nuclear Science, IEEE Transactions on, IEEE Trans. Nucl. Sci, 70(6), pp. 1069–1074. doi:10.1109/TNS.2022.3224766.
          </tr>
