            <td>2
            <td>Continuous Delivery
            <td>Continuous Delivery refers to the automated process of building, testing, and deploying software. It allows for the timely release of high-quality software to various runtime infrastructures.
            <td>Isaac Sacolick. (APR 15, 2022). What is CI/CD? Continuous integration and continuous delivery explained. Infoworld. https://www.infoworld.com/article/3271126/what-is-cicd-continuous-integration-and-continuous-delivery-explained.html<br/><br/>
              Pastrana Pardo, M. A., Erazo, H. A. O., & Lozada, C. A. C. (2022). Teaching Guide for Beginnings in DevOps and Continuous Delivery in AWS Focused on the Society 5.0 Skillset. IEEE Revista Iberoamericana de Tecnologias Del Aprendizaje, Tecnologias Del Aprendizaje, IEEE Revista Iberoamericana de, IEEE R. Iberoamericana Tecnologias Aprendizaje, 17(4), 358–370. https://doi.org/10.1109/RITA.2022.3217172
          </tr>
