            <td>3
            <td>Containerization
            <td>Containerization is the process of packaging applications and their dependencies into portable, isolated containers. It allows application runs across different environments and enhances the efficiency and collaboration between development and operations teams. Using containerization offers several advantages such as portability, heightened security, and better utilization of resources.
            <td>Simplilearn. (Dec 20, 2022). What is Containerization?. Simplilearn. https://www.simplilearn.com/what-is-containerization-article<br/><br/>
              Arrichiello, A. author. (2022). Podman for DevOps : containerization reimagined with Podman and its companion tools / Alessandro Arrichiello, Gianni Salinetti. Packt Publishing. 
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>4
            <td>Microservices
            <td>Microservices is a software architecture approach that involves breaking down complex tasks into smaller, independent, and specific tasks. Microservices offer greater flexibility, scalability, and easier management.
            <td>Namit Tanasseri, & Rahul Rai. (2017). Microservices with Azure : Architect Enterprise-grade, Microservice-based Solutions Using Microsoft Azure Service Fabric. Packt Publishing. 
          </tr>
